'''Vesicouretic reflux''' is a condition in which normal compression of the [[urinary bladder|bladder]] during urination results in an abnormal backflow of urine into the [[kidney]]s.  It is the second most common renal disease in children.<ref Name="Trull">{{cite book
  | last =Trull
  | first =
